Reasoning: The paper deals with theoretical convergence guarantees for temporal difference (TD) learning with nonlinear function approximation. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and specifically reinforcement learning. The paper discusses the expected dynamics of the TD(0) algorithm and proves convergence results for certain types of nonlinear function approximators. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
